---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'

import location from '~/assets/banners/location.jpg'
import hertz from '~/assets/hertz.jpg'

import Layout from '~/layouts/Base.astro'
---

<Layout>
  <div class="banner" style={{ backgroundImage: `url(${location.src})` }}>
    <p>
      <code>exec(ut)</code> will be hosted in Hertz, TivoliVredenburg<br />
      <a href="#directions" title="Travel Directions"><button class="button">Travel directions</button></a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="copy" id="two-column">
    <div class="column" id="main">
      <h1>About TivoliVredenburg</h1>

      <p>
        As the <code>(ut)</code> in <code>exec(ut)</code> suggests the conference is to be hosted in Utrecht. The venue of the event will be the renowned TivoliVredenburg, which is located a stone's throw away from Utrecht Central Station. Both Hertz and Plein6, the networking area/barzone, will be at our disposal throughout the day.
      </p>

      <p>
        Hertz is built for listening to everything worthwhile, whether it's classical concerts or conference talks. Of course you will have ample time to test the seats and verify our sales-pitch throughout the day.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="column" id="side">
      <h1>Hertz</h1>
      <Image src={hertz} class="impression" alt="Hertz - TivoliVredenburg" />
    </div>

    <div class="column" id="fullwidth">
      <h1 id="directions">Travel directions</h1>
      <p>
        <code>
          TivoliVredenburg<br />
          Vredenburgkade 11<br />
          3511WC, Utrecht<br />
          The Netherlands
        </code>
      </p>

      <iframe
        src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2451.302294570152!2d5.110242177853186!3d52.0924297719522!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47c66f42e80b5a65%3A0xcb73f73b5ccc3eb6!2sTivoliVredenburg!5e0!3m2!1sen!2snl!4v1760629484870!5m2!1sen!2snl"
        style={{ width: '100%', height: '250px', border: 0 }}
        allowfullscreen
        loading="lazy"
        referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
